# Change completeness (core-be)

A change is **not done** when the code compiles and one test passes. It is done when
**every artifact that mirrors the change has moved with it.** A single fact in this repo
is often stated in code, its own test, a cross-cutting test, a doc, and a skill at once —
edit only the code and the other four go stale, invisibly, until CI or a human trips over it.

## Before you call a change done, walk the five layers

1. **Its own tests — at the right layer.** Add/update/delete the directly-covering test in the
   layer the pyramid dictates (pure → `src/tests/unit/` or co-located `__tests__/unit/`;
   route/DB → domain `__tests__/*.test.ts`). No test delta is a red flag — name why (pure
   rename, comment-only, or an existing assertion that already covers it). Skill: **test-generator**.
2. **Cross-cutting tests.** Check whether a shared suite also asserts the change and update it
   (or confirm it stays green by design): `src/tests/security/`, `src/tests/integration/`,
   `src/tests/global/` (repo-wide invariants), `src/tests/contract/`, `src/tests/chaos/`,
   `src/tests/load/k6/scenarios/`, `src/tests/performance/`. Test the mechanism **once** at the
   layer that owns it on a representative case — do not fan the same assertion across every suite.
3. **Docs.** Update the nearest `src/**/OVERVIEW.md`, the relevant `docs/reference/**`, TSDoc on
   any added/renamed export (`pnpm tsdoc:check`), route `schema` blocks, and `.env.example` for new env vars.
4. **Rules.** If the change alters a convention or an enforced count, update the relevant
   `agent-os/rules/*.mdc`. Skill: **structure-maintainer**.
5. **Skills.** If you added/renamed a skill, or a skill hardcodes a fact you changed (a count, a
   route set, a path list), update it and the indexes: `agent-os/skills/skill-index/SKILL.md`
   (count + table), `agent-os/skills/groups.json`, `agent-os/docs/skill-triggers.md`, and the
   `N project skills` count in `CLAUDE.md` / `AGENTS.md`. Gate: `pnpm agent-os:check`.

## Find every mirror

When a single fact (a count, a route path, a constant, an env key, a header) moves, **grep the
literal repo-wide** across `src/`, `docs/`, and `agent-os/` and fix every stale duplicate — this
is the most common miss. Consult **[skill-index](../skills/skill-index/SKILL.md)** first to route
the files you touched to their owner skill(s), then let the gates catch the rest: `pnpm validate`,
`pnpm test:global`, `pnpm routes:catalog:check`, `pnpm tsdoc:check`, `pnpm agent-os:check`,
`pnpm guard:pre-commit`. Treat a gate failure as a mirror you missed, not noise.

Full detail: **[change-completeness-guard](../skills/change-completeness-guard/SKILL.md)**.
